Autus Asset Management LLC Sells 2,535 Shares of Emerson Electric Company (EMR)

Posted by Dan Jones on Jul 24th, 2017 // No Comments 

Autus Asset Management LLC lowered its stake in shares of Emerson Electric Company (NYSE:EMR) by 7.7% during the first quarter, according to its most recent Form 13F filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission. The firm owned 30,347 shares of the industrial products company’s stock after selling 2,535 shares during the period. Autus Asset Management LLC’s holdings in Emerson Electric were worth $1,816,000 at the end of the most recent reporting period. 
Several other large investors also recently made changes to their positions in the stock. Northwest Quadrant Wealth Management LLC bought a new position in shares of Emerson Electric during the fourth quarter worth approximately $111,000. Edge Asset Management Inc. increased its stake in shares of Emerson Electric by 4.4% in the fourth quarter. Edge Asset Management Inc. now owns 896,565 shares of the industrial products company’s stock valued at $49,983,000 after buying an additional 37,972 shares during the last quarter. Bayesian Capital Management LP acquired a new stake in shares of Emerson Electric during the fourth quarter valued at $981,000. Stone Run Capital LLC increased its stake in shares of Emerson Electric by 10.4% in the fourth quarter. Stone Run Capital LLC now owns 99,150 shares of the industrial products company’s stock valued at $5,527,000 after buying an additional 9,300 shares during the last quarter. Finally, Iberiabank Corp increased its stake in shares of Emerson Electric by 10.1% in the fourth quarter. Iberiabank Corp now owns 66,944 shares of the industrial products company’s stock valued at $3,732,000 after buying an additional 6,138 shares during the last quarter. 68.87% of the stock is owned by institutional investors and hedge funds. 


 Get Emerson Electric Company alerts:



Shares of Emerson Electric Company (NYSE:EMR) traded down 0.43% during mid-day trading on Friday, hitting $60.04. The stock had a trading volume of 2,280,835 shares. Emerson Electric Company has a 1-year low of $49.22 and a 1-year high of $64.36. The company has a market cap of $38.69 billion, a P/E ratio of 25.65 and a beta of 1.20. The firm’s 50 day moving average price is $59.68 and its 200 day moving average price is $59.54. 




Emerson Electric (NYSE:EMR) last issued its quarterly earnings results on Tuesday, May 2nd. The industrial products company reported $0.58 earnings per share for the quarter, hitting the Zacks’ consensus estimate of $0.58. Emerson Electric had a return on equity of 23.37% and a net margin of 8.72%. The firm had revenue of $3.57 billion during the quarter, compared to the consensus estimate of $3.49 billion. During the same period last year, the business posted $0.57 EPS. The business’s revenue was down .1% compared to the same quarter last year. Analysts predict that Emerson Electric Company will post $2.60 earnings per share for the current fiscal year. 
COPYRIGHT VIOLATION NOTICE: “Autus Asset Management LLC Sells 2,535 Shares of Emerson Electric Company (EMR)” was originally published by BNB Daily and is the sole property of of BNB Daily. If you are reading this news story on another publication, it was copied illegally and republished in violation of international trademark & copyright legislation. The legal version of this news story can be viewed at https://www.baseball-news-blog.com/2017/07/24/emerson-electric-company-emr-shares-sold-by-autus-asset-management-llc-updated-updated.html. 
A number of analysts have commented on the company. TheStreet upgraded Emerson Electric from a “c+” rating to a “b” rating in a research report on Thursday, May 4th. Zacks Investment Research downgraded Emerson Electric from a “buy” rating to a “hold” rating in a research report on Friday, May 5th. Royal Bank Of Canada restated a “hold” rating and set a $62.00 target price on shares of Emerson Electric in a research report on Tuesday, June 6th. Cowen and Company reaffirmed a “hold” rating and set a $62.00 price target on shares of Emerson Electric in a report on Tuesday, April 25th. Finally, JMP Securities started coverage on Emerson Electric in a research note on Monday, June 19th. They issued an “outperform” rating and a $70.00 target price for the company. Three investment analysts have rated the stock with a sell rating, fifteen have given a hold rating and three have issued a buy rating to the company. Emerson Electric has a consensus rating of “Hold” and an average target price of $56.96.
Emerson Electric Company Profile
Emerson Electric Co is a diversified global manufacturing company, which provides solutions to customers by bringing technology and engineering together in the industrial, commercial and consumer markets around the world. The Company operates through four segments based on the nature of the products and services rendered: Process Management, Industrial Automation, Climate Technologies and Commercial & Residential Solutions. 

 
